# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
When add edge from a to b, distance is w,
for all pair`(i, j)`the distance change is `i->a` + `a->b` + `b->j` 

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Constructor, using dijkstra algorithm to build all pair`(i, j)` distance, 
   and stored into `dist[i][j]`
2. function: `addEdge(a, b, w)`
   case 1: `dist[a][b] <= w`, directly return.

   case 2: `dist[a][b] > w`, update `dist[a][b] = w`
   scan all of pairs(i, j) update `dist[i][j]`
   ```
   for(int i = 0 ;  i < n ; i++)
      for(int j = 0 ; j < n ; j++)
          dist[i][j] = dist[i][a] + dist[a][b] + dist[b][j]);
   ```
3. function: `shortestPath(node1, node2)`
   directly return `dist[node1][node2]`

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(max(Elog(V), V ^ 2)) (Dijkstra)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(max(E + V, V ^ 2))
