solutions.content:
Compute the single-source-shortest-paths upon demand for each query from source `s` to target `t`.

* Bellman-Ford results in TLE
* SPFA (shortest paths faster algorithm) is AC
    * this is a natural progression from Bellman-Ford, ie. we only attempt to relax candidate edges (instead of all edges)

---

**Bellman-Ford (TLE) Solutions:**

*Kotlin*
```
class Graph(N: Int, E: Array<IntArray>) {
    private var N = N
    private var E = E.toMutableList()
    private var INF = 1e9.toInt() + 7
    fun addEdge(edge: IntArray) {
        E.add(edge)
    }
    fun shortestPath(s: Int, t: Int): Int {
        var dist = IntArray(N) { INF }
        dist[s] = 0
        for (k in 0 until N - 1)
            for ((u, v, w) in E)
                if (dist[v] > dist[u] + w)
                    dist[v] = dist[u] + w
        return if (dist[t] < INF) dist[t] else -1
    }
}
```

