Dijkstra to answer each query would suffice, along with an AL for quick evaluation of the neighbors of each node.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We update the AL each time addEdge is called, and do a dijkstra each time shortestPath is called.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1) for addEdge, O((V+E)logV) for each shortestPath

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1) for addEdge, O(V) for each shortestPath

