**Method 2:** Arithmetic Progression 
* Sum of an AP whose first term = a, common difference = a and number of terms = floor(n/a) is `a (n/a) (n/a + 1) / 2`
* This can be derived as follows:
	* S = a + 2a + ... + Ta = a (1 + 2 + ... + T) = aT(T + 1) / 2, where T = n / a
	* T = n / a because final term can at max be n = aT
>**T/S:** O(1)/O(1)
```
public int sumOfMultiples(int n) {
	return sum(n, 3) + sum(n, 5) + sum(n, 7) - sum(n, 15) - sum(n, 35) - sum(n, 21) + sum(n, 105);
}

private int sum(int max, int firstTerm) {
	return firstTerm * (max / firstTerm) * (max / firstTerm + 1) / 2;
}
```
