Let's break down the code and its components
``` 
var createHelloWorld = function() {
      // ...
      };
``` 
- This code declares a variable called createHelloWorld and assigns it to an anonymous function. 
- This anonymous function will be returned when createHelloWorld is called.
``` 
return function(...args) {
      return "Hello World";
      }

}
```
- This is the nested function that will be returned when createHelloWorld is called. 
- The ...args syntax is used to accept any number of arguments passed to the function, 
- although in this case, the arguments are not used in the function's logic. 
- Instead, the function simply returns the string "Hello World" when called.


```
 const f = createHelloWorld();
f(); // "Hello World"

