# Intuition
You are returning an array of subarrays. So, we should build up a subarray until the subarray is of length ```size```, then push that subarray to the main array. Repeat.

# Approach
1. Create array ```answer``` (array being returned) and array ```cur``` (subarray variable)
2. Iterate through ```arr``` until ```cur``` is of length ```size```
3. Push subarray ```cur``` to ```answer```, reset ```cur``` to an empty array so we can create the next subarray
4. Repeat steps 2 & 3 until iterated throughout all of ```arr```
5. If ```cur``` is not empty, we did not push the subarray we have been building. Since the problem wants us to push the remainding items of ```arr```, we push what we got in ```cur```

# Code
```
/**
 * @param {Array} arr
 * @param {number} size
 * @return {Array[]}
 */
var chunk = function(arr, size) {
    var answer = [];
    var cur = [];

    // iterate through arr
    for (var i = 0; i < arr.length; ++i) {
        cur.push(arr[i]);

        // if subarray is of length size, push our subarray
        if (cur.length === size) {
            answer.push(cur);
            cur = [];
        }
