# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

We can use the native `Array.slice()` method to create chunked arrays out of the original one. Slice takes as parameters a starting index and an ending index to create a subarray.

Since we want chunked arrays of size `size`, we iterate through `arr`, and every time we create a chunked array of starting index `i `and end index `i + size`, we increment `i` by `size` and repeat the process. Each time a chunked array is created, we push it to `result`, and in the end, we return `result`.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n2)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
/**
 * @param {Array} arr
 * @param {number} size
