# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Iterate through entire array, create new mini array once previous mini array has reached the length = size

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Read the comments in the code. It's pretty clear.


# Code
```
/**
 * @param {Array} arr
 * @param {number} size
 * @return {Array[]}
 */
var chunk = function(arr, size) {

    let finalArr = [];
    let numMinis = arr.length/size;
    // used for mini arrays
    let temp = [];

    // edge case where the original array is empty 
    if(arr.length === 0){
        return arr;
    }
    // keeps track of mini array size 
    let j = 0;
    for(let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++){
        if(j < size){
            // add value to the mini array
            temp.push(arr[i]);
            j++;
            // console.log(`j = ${j} < size = ${size}: temp = ${temp}`)
        } else{
            // add the mini array to the final array
            finalArr.push(temp);
            // "create"" new empty array 
            temp = [];
            // set j to 0
            j = 0;
            // add value to mini array 
            temp.push(arr[i])
            j++;
        }

    }
    // edge case where the size is greater than the original array's length
    // the last mini array is less than or equal to the size
    if((arr.length < size) || (temp.length <= size)){
        finalArr.push(temp);
    }


    return finalArr;
};
```

