This is a rather plain problem where we need to implement a factory function to produce objects based on one value (`val`).

Each object will have a method taking another parameter (`otherVal`) as required that will either:
* `return` `true` if the specified condition is met;
* `throw` the error in the specs otherwise.

And we can do it all with arrow functions, because why not?

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(1)$$
- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$

# Code
```ts
type ToBeOrNotToBe = {
    toBe: (val: any) => boolean;
    notToBe: (val: any) => boolean;
};

const expect = (val: any): ToBeOrNotToBe => ({
    toBe: (otherVal) => {
        if (otherVal === val) return true;
        throw "Not Equal";
    },
    notToBe: (otherVal) => {
        if (otherVal !== val) return true;
        throw "Equal";
    }
});
```

